{
  "texts": [
    "For case 3 one needs multiple, very distinct mass peaks.",
    "Images always appear and disappear in pairs: a saddle point and either a maximum or minimum.",
    "Thus, the number of images is always odd.",
    "Although the number of images is always odd, the number of observable images may not be.",
    "This is because different images are variously magnified, and some images can be demagnified so much that they cannot be detected anymore."
  ]
}